text: Richard Holland (c. 1549–1618), of Denton Hall, Manchester and Heaton Hall, Lancashire, was an English politician. He was a Member (MP) of the Parliament of England for Lancashire in 1586. ==References== Category:1549 births Category:1618 deaths Category:English MPs 1586–1587 Category:Members of the Parliament of England (pre-1707) for Lancashire
